articles.description: Peyton Aldridge had 23 points and 11 rebounds for his second double-double, Kellan Grady scored 19 points and Davidson pulled away from VCU for a 74-63 win Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Aldridge, Grady lead Davidson past VCU 74-63

articles.description: Senior Patrick Steeves scored 16 points with 12 rebounds for his first career double-double, Terry Nolan Jr. added 12 points with six assists and three steals, and George Washington beat Massachusetts 83-72 on Wednesday night to win its fifth straight...
articles.headline: George Washington downs UMass 83-72

articles.description: Vanderbilt guard Riley LaChance joins SEC Now to describe what his game-winning shot felt like and how the team's game plan has changed throughout the season.
articles.headline: LaChance's late three sinks Bulldogs

articles.description: Stefan Kenic scored a career-high 19 points, Anthony Wright added 15 with 12 rebounds, and Cleveland State held off Detroit Mercy 75-72 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Cleveland St holds off Detroit 75-72 on Kenic's career night

articles.description: Grayson Allen scored 25 points and matched a career high with seven 3-pointers, helping No. 12 Duke beat Virginia Tech 74-52 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Allen, No. 12 Duke beat Virginia Tech 74-52 without Bagley

videos.description: Kassius Robertson zig-zags on top the key for an easy 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Missouri's Robertson drains easy triple

videos.description: Avery Johnson Jr. drives in for a running hook shot.
videos.headline: Alabama's Johnson drives in for hook shot

videos.description: Cullen VanLeer kicks it out to Jordan Barnett who makes the wide-open 3-pointer from the wing, giving Missouri a 29-19 lead.
videos.headline: Tigers Barnett sinks wide-open three

videos.description: Reed Nikko takes advantage of Alabama's bad communication and slams one home for a soft two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Good screen play leads to Missouri's Nikko dunk

videos.description: Braxton Key passes the ball off to Galin Smith who throws it down for a two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Crimson Tide responds with a dunk made by Smith

videos.description: Collin Sexton contests the inbound pass, and Dazon Ingram drives it home for a great layup.
videos.headline: Great steal-and-score play made by Alabama

videos.description: Collin Sexton drains a deep three for his 11th point in the first half, making it a three-point game.
videos.headline: Alabama's Sexton buries three before half

videos.description: Collin Sexton yells out that he is open and drains three-pointer from the wing.
videos.headline: Alabama's good communication leads to easy three

videos.description: Jeremiah Tilmon keeps his hands up the entire time when two players attempt to make a shot and swats the Alabama lay-in attempt away.
videos.headline: Great block made by Missouri's Tilmon

videos.description: Jeremiah Tilmon impresses with a beautiful reverse spin to juke out his defender for a two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Tigers' Tilmon spins his way into a dunk
